<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-08T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="818" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d818">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.61/164: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-08T19:00:00+03:00">January 8,
                                    1941—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received January 8—3:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>31. My telegram 30, January 8, 6 p.m. I have had a further talk with
                            Lozovzki this evening with respect to the difficulties which the Embassy
                            has been encountering and which have not as yet been disposed of. He
                            assured me that he would give these matters his personal attention in
                            the course of the next few days and would endeavor to dispose of them to
                            my satisfaction.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>